author.value: Collection processed by Zachary Dabbs, 2009; collection processed by Brent Phillips, 2009. Media updates by Rhyannon Rodriguez, 2009.

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2019-08-19T14:14:46</date>

extent.value: in 59 record cartons, 1 half manuscript box, and 1 flat box.

abstract.value: The Bob Holman Audio/ Video Poetry Collection is a multimedia collection documenting spoken word performances and productions between the years 1977 and 2002. Key items include spoken word projects produced by Bob Holman.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the
following form:<lb/><lb/>
Identification of item,  date (if known); Bob Holman Audio/ Video Poetry Collection; MSS 128; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.
Original gift donated in 2009. Accretions donated in 2015 and 2018. The accession numbers associated with these accretions are 2015.128 and 2018.067.

Subseries E: Vinyl Recordings - Allen Ginsberg is composed of a collection of spoken word and musical recordings previousky owned by Allen Ginsberg, which Holman purchased at a Sotheby's auction in October of 1999.
